The paper focuses on developing deep learning models for grade prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The models are evaluated on data collected from a large public university, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the importance of personalized feedback for students, which may involve natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper explores the development of an educational early warning system, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of computer science education (cs.EDU).
